post_cb({"8146647": {"CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2011-11-16T04:16:21.190", "PostTypeId": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "8146736", "LastEditorUserId": "985032", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-06T11:33:45.533", "LastEditDate": "2011-11-16T12:00:55.520", "ViewCount": "185", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Need quote from standard about legality of main function as a template function", "Id": "8146647", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>On a whim, I tried to define the main function as a template function using clang 2.9:</p>\n<pre><code>template &lt;typename T = void&gt;\nint main(int argc, char **argv)\n{\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>and received the following error.</p>\n<pre><code>error: 'main' cannot be a template\nint main(int argc, char **argv)\n    ^\n</code></pre>\n<p>Does anyone know what section of the standard forbids this, and what the relevant text is?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><templates><c++11><clang><main>", "OwnerUserId": "985032", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "8146736": {"ParentId": "8146647", "CommentCount": "6", "Body": "<p>Well, how about this (3.6.1):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_8146647_8146736_0\">A program shall contain a global function called main, which is the designated start of the program. [...] This function shall not be overloaded. It shall have a return type of type int, but otherwise its type is implementation-defined.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Since templates are not functions, I don't think you have any choice in the matter. In particular, the function has to be <code>main</code>, not <code>main&lt;&gt;</code> as in your example; and your <code>main</code> isn't a function, but a template, precluding the existence of another function called <code>main</code>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "596781", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "8146736", "Score": "15", "CreationDate": "2011-11-16T04:28:01.840", "LastActivityDate": "2011-11-16T04:28:01.840"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_8146647_8146736_0": {"section_id": 7146, "quality": 0.55, "length": 11}}, "n3337": {"so_8146647_8146736_0": {"section_id": 6890, "quality": 0.55, "length": 11}}, "n4659": {"so_8146647_8146736_0": {"section_id": 8647, "quality": 0.55, "length": 11}}}, "8146966": {"ParentId": "8146647", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2011-11-16T05:02:52.677", "Score": "-7", "LastEditorUserId": "759866", "LastEditDate": "2013-12-06T11:33:45.533", "Id": "8146966", "OwnerUserId": "1048960", "Body": "<p>Function templates must be declared in .h file.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-06T11:33:45.533"}});